<quantity box="[1083,1203,1793,1817]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="45.5" valueMax="54.0" valueMin="37.0">37–54 mm</quantity>
. Base color yellow dark pattern reduced; telson brown; chelicerae pale yellow without reticulation. Pedipalp movable fingers bear 10–11 rows of granules, with 12 outer and inner denticles and fixed finger with 10–11 outer and inner denticles. Chela of pedipalp narrower in male, its length to width ratio 3.4–3.6 in females and 4.1–4.3 in males. Telson bulbous, with aculeus shorter than vesicle. Pectinal teeth number 
<quantity box="[1048,1140,2017,2041]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.858" metricValueMax="7.366" metricValueMin="6.35" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="27.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="25.0">25–29 in</quantity>
females and 
<quantity box="[1278,1370,2017,2041]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.001" metricValueMax="8.89" metricValueMin="7.112" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="31.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="28.0">28–35 in</quantity>
males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[113,771,538,914]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
COMMENTS. 
<bibRefCitation author="LEVY, G. &amp; P. AMITAI" bookContentInfo="132 pp." box="[246,536,538,563]" journalOrPublisher="Jerusalem: The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" refId="ref10220" refString="LEVY, G. &amp; P. AMITAI. 1980. Fauna Palaestina, Arachnida I. - Scorpiones. Jerusalem: The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, 132 pp." title="Fauna Palaestina, Arachnida I. - Scorpiones." type="book" year="1980">Levy &amp; Amitai (1980: 21)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="occitanus" subSpecies="zeylensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus occitanus zeylensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pocock" box="[343,498,570,594]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="occitanus" subSpecies="berberensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus occitanus berberensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pocock" box="[250,405,602,626]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. They argued that “examination of Pocock´s 
<typeStatus box="[255,311,635,659]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">types</typeStatus>
and of additional material from 
<collectingCountry box="[684,771,634,658]" name="Somalia" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Somalia</collectingCountry>
showed that these two forms are in fact the two sexes of the same subspecies, the first the male, the second the female.” We studied in detail a large collection of Somaliland specimens collected during expeditions of 2011–2019; this study, including cytogenetic and DNA analysis, confirmed that these two taxa are valid species. Here, we restore 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="occitanus" subSpecies="zeylensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus occitanus zeylensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pocock" box="[323,468,858,882]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from synonymy and elevate it to species rank.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[113,771,954,1426]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">
COMMENTS ON LOCALITIES AND LIFE STRATEGY. In 2019, two of us (FK, HE) visited the city of Zeyla, the 
<typeStatus box="[604,651,987,1011]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock, 1900" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" box="[113,454,1018,1042]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylensis">
<emphasis box="[113,294,1018,1042]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus zeylensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pocock" box="[301,454,1018,1042]" firstAuthor="Pocock" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 63" refId="ref10359" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1900. On a collection of insects and arachnids made in 1895 and 1897 by Mr. C. A. V. Peel, F. Z. S. in Somaliland, with descriptions of new species. 10. General list of the scorpions of Somaliland and the Boran Country. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 1900: 55 - 63." type="book chapter" year="1900">Pocock, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is an extremely hot place, with heavily salted soils. We collected scorpions several km from the city (
<geoCoordinate box="[275,423,1082,1106]" degrees="11" direction="north" minutes="19" orientation="latitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" precision="1" seconds="31.2" value="11.325334">11°19'31.2&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[433,579,1082,1106]" degrees="43" direction="east" minutes="22" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" precision="1" seconds="16.9" value="43.37136">43°22'16.9&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
) and found there 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pocock, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[113,532,1114,1138]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Hottentotta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polystictus">
<emphasis box="[113,360,1114,1138]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Hottentotta polystictus</emphasis>
(Pocock, 1896)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pavesi, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Pavesi" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Microbuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litoralis">
<emphasis box="[541,771,1114,1138]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Microbuthus litoralis</emphasis>
(Pavesi, 1885)
</taxonomicName>
(first record for Somaliland), 
<taxonomicName authority="KovarIk et Lowe, 2016" authorityName="KovarIk et Lowe" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afar">
<emphasis box="[587,771,1146,1170]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Orthochirus afar</emphasis>
KovařÍk et Lowe, 2016
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pocock, 1895" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Parabuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granimanus">
<emphasis box="[415,678,1178,1202]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Parabuthus granimanus</emphasis>
Pocock, 1895
</taxonomicName>
(topotypes) but no 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[382,457,1210,1234]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[382,457,1210,1234]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1900" box="[592,771,1210,1234]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylensis">
<emphasis box="[592,771,1210,1234]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Buthus zeylensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is common in Gerissa, a very hot, sandy semidesert area (
<figureCitation box="[121,217,1274,1298]" captionStart="Figures 100–101" captionStartId="17.[113,190,2013,2035]" captionTargetBox="[113,1474,234,1995]" captionTargetId="figure-35@17.[113,1474,234,1998]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figures 100–101: Localities. Figure 100. Buthus pococki sp. n., type locality (19SC). Figure 101. B. zeylensis, locality 19SH." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648410/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
) where we recorded also 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[512,666,1274,1298]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Hottentotta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polystictus">
<emphasis box="[512,666,1274,1298]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">H. polystictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KovarIk et Lowe" authorityYear="2016" box="[683,764,1274,1298]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afar">
<emphasis box="[683,764,1274,1298]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">O. afar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" box="[165,328,1307,1330]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Parabuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granimanus">
<emphasis box="[165,328,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">P. granimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but also 
<taxonomicName authority="KovarIk, 2012" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2012" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Compsobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="somalilandus">
<emphasis box="[452,771,1306,1330]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Compsobuthus somalilandus</emphasis>
KovařÍk, 2012
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="KovarIk et al., 2018" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2018" box="[290,705,1338,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Gint" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gubanensis">
<emphasis box="[290,470,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Gint gubanensis</emphasis>
KovařÍk et al., 2018
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[723,771,1338,1362]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
locality), and 
<taxonomicName authority="KovarIk et al., 2018" authorityName="KovarIk" authorityYear="2018" box="[275,771,1370,1397]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Neobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="32" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gubanensis">
<emphasis box="[275,525,1370,1394]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">Neobuthus gubanensis</emphasis>
KovařÍk et al., 2018
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[121,169,1402,1426]" pageId="32" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
locality).
</paragraph>
